verbose_text: Because a dynamic cycle of activation-inhibition of Cdc42 drives the priming of FEME, Cdc42 inhibitors can either be stimulatory or inhibitory (depending on concentrations and incubation times) [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], and thus are not a reliable way of controlling the pathway.
evidence: Cdc42 drives the priming of FEME
